structure.name: Population Clock Component Data
structure.description: Statistics about the population and components of change (births, deaths, migration) for Australia and its states and territories. Unit of measure: Persons. Geographic coverage: Australia/State. Catalogue number: 3101.0

descriptions.en: Statistics about the population and components of change (births, deaths, migration) for Australia and its states and territories. Unit of measure: Persons. Geographic coverage: Australia/State. Catalogue number: 3101.0

annotations.text: Dataset contains annual data for the year ending in the quarter specified.

annotations.text: The measurement represented by each observation corresponds to a specific point in time (e.g. a single day) or a period (e.g. a month, a fiscal year, or a calendar year).
